Magician of the 22nd lvl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukassinova.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kassinova</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/01 8:13:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   WW</span><hr size=1> You can go to Warsilk Woods off from OT and hunt the brutes.  I had a friend of mine that did them and he said they were great.  They were a static spawn also.  May want to swing by there and con them see if you can solo them....exp has to be great. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uniden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Niden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/01 9:10:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels2428.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Sure.</span><hr size=1> As my esteemed colleage suggested, the skulking brutes in the caves that lead to the Crypt of Dalnir are a fantastic soloing spot.  They are do not aggro or assist, and are fairly easy to defeat for their level.  You do have to be careful to kill them quickly when they start to walk away, as there is a bug in the environment which will allow him to walk inside the wall and then be able to hit you anywhere in the zone without you being able to kill him.  I would wait until you reached level 24 before fighting here.<br>
<br>
In your early 20's, there are fewer places to solo, but it's a bit sparse if you rule out the Karanas, especially since one of the easiest places to fight to 24 is the hermit in South Karana.  That said, you might try the mammoths in Everfrost, as the tusks are good money and soloable right around that level.  Another place you might check out is Lake Rathetear -- the aviak guards there should take you to 24.<br>
<br>
I can't think of anything else off the top of my head.  You'd do well to get some group experience under your belt at early levels -- it will help you later on when grouping starts to become a lot more appealing.<br>
<br>
-nid <p><hr align="left" size="1" width="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#2f2f2f">
